arcana (0.20.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: AI provider code extracted into a new shard, arcana-ai.
    All AI types moved from `Arcana::*` to `Arcana::AI::*`
    (`Arcana::Chat::Anthropic` -> `Arcana::AI::Chat::Anthropic`, etc).
    Consumers of the AI code as a Crystal library need to update
    imports and namespace references. Bus-service semantics are
    unchanged — `openai:chat`, `anthropic:chat`, etc. still work the
    same over the wire.
  * The `arcana:registry` bus service is removed. `arcana_directory`
    (or POST /directory) plus per-service `_intent: "help"` cover
    what it was used for. `Arcana::AI::Registry` remains as the
    programmatic factory in arcana-ai.
  * arcana now depends on arcana-ai ~> 0.1.0.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.19.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New built-in service `arcana:help` — like 411 for the bus. Send an
    empty payload to get the full workflow briefing (register, discover,
    deliver, receive, addressing, errors). Optional `topic` param drills
    into one section: workflow, addressing, discovery, errors. `topic:
    "list"` returns the available topic names. Unknown topics return
    the valid list in the error. Lets non-MCP bus clients self-onboard
    without needing the MCP initialize briefing.
  * Briefing text is now a shared `Arcana::Help::BRIEFING` constant
    used by both the MCP initialize response and the arcana:help
    service, so the two surfaces can't drift.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Wed, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.19.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * /send and /deliver now suggest the closest registered address
    when delivery fails for an unknown one. The 404 response includes
    a structured `did_you_mean: {address, name, description}` field
    and an updated human-readable error string ("...Did you mean 'X'
    (Name)?"). Scoring is substring-containment-first, then
    Levenshtein-normalized; below a similarity threshold the response
    is unchanged. Addresses the recurring case where agents
    re-register under different names and senders retry stale ones.
  * MCP `initialize` instructions briefing now mentions the
    `did_you_mean` field so agents react to it on delivery failure.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Thu, 28 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.19.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * anthropic:chat now accepts a `web_search: true` flag. When set,
    Claude can search the web during its response (the model decides
    when/whether). The response shape is unchanged — ask in the
    prompt for whatever format you want (e.g. JSON with a `url`
    field). Useful for fact lookup, finding canonical URLs, current
    events.
  * MCP server now returns an `instructions` field in the initialize
    response — a one-time workflow briefing ("register first, then
    deliver/receive, use arcana_directory for discovery") that the
    client carries as standing context. Tool descriptions stay
    focused on per-tool behavior instead of repeatedly explaining
    the same setup.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Sun, 24 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.19.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix migration runner: it used crystal-pg's prepared exec which is
    one-statement-only, so any migration file with more than one SQL
    statement (e.g. the init_auth schema with its 4 tables + indexes)
    failed at apply time with "cannot insert multiple commands into
    a prepared statement". Now splits on `;` and runs each statement
    in the same transaction.
  * Fix migration directory resolution: previously preferred
    $CWD/db/migrations even when empty, which silently masked a
    real install. Now prefers /usr/share/arcana/db/migrations and
    only falls back to CWD when running from a source checkout
    (shard.yml present).
  * No schema changes. Existing 0.19.0 deployments with the manually
    applied init_auth schema will see `schema_migrations` filled in
    on next migrate (no-op for the table contents).

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Wed, 20 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.19.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Server-side bearer-token auth (stage 2 of 3 for SaaS auth).
    Set ARCANA_AUTH_REQUIRED=1 to require a valid
    `Authorization: Bearer ak_...` header on every REST call and
    WebSocket upgrade. /health remains open for liveness probes.
    Requires ARCANA_DATABASE_URL — the server refuses to start with
    auth enabled and no identity store.
  * Auth is fully opt-in. With ARCANA_AUTH_REQUIRED unset, the bus
    behaves exactly as before — anonymous access, single-tenant
    localhost. No breaking change for existing deployments.
  * Failed auth attempts are recorded as `auth.failed` events
    (transport=rest|websocket) for audit.
  * arcana-mcp bridge now forwards ARCANA_API_KEY as a bearer token
    on every HTTP call, so MCP clients work against an
    auth-enforcing server.
  * Per-listing / per-org tenancy isolation intentionally deferred
    to stage 3.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Sat, 16 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.18.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * arcana now auto-runs pending migrations on startup when
    ARCANA_DATABASE_URL is set. Future schema changes ship via
    db/migrations/*.sql and apply on the next service restart.
    Migration failure is fatal (loud, easy to diagnose).
  * New helper script: arcana-init-db. Interactive Postgres bootstrap:
    starts the cluster, creates the database and role, writes
    ARCANA_DATABASE_URL into /etc/arcana/arcana.env, runs migrate,
    optionally creates a platform admin key. Idempotent; re-runs are
    safe.
  * Install hook now mentions arcana-init-db as the optional path
    to enable auth.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Mon, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.18.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Identity / org / API key foundation (stage 1 of 3 for SaaS auth).
  * New optional Postgres dependency, configured via
    ARCANA_DATABASE_URL. When unset, no behavior change — current
    single-tenant localhost users keep working.
  * New tables: orgs, users, memberships, api_keys.
  * New CLI: arcana-admin (migrate, org/user/member/key subcommands).
  * Server-side auth enforcement intentionally deferred to stage 2.
  * SQL migrations install to /usr/share/arcana/db/migrations/.
  * Adds runtime dep: pg ~> 0.29.0 (will/crystal-pg).

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.17.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add `listed: false` to /register and the WebSocket join frame.
    Pure consumers (web apps, scripts) can now register a mailbox
    without polluting the directory with an entry nobody will look up.
  * MCP arcana_register tool gains `listed` param.
  * Snapshot loader drops legacy "<name>:service" entries instead of
    rewriting them to "<name>:legacy" — preserving stale entries
    under a fake owner was misleading. Re-register cleanly.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.5.1.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.16.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Snapshot now goes through Arcana::StateBackend instead of writing
    files directly. Default backend (LocalFileBackend) preserves the
    current behavior — single file, atomic tmp+rename. Future
    Postgres or S3 backends drop in without touching Snapshot.
  * Default event-log sweep interval bumped from 6h to 24h. Lower it
    via ARCANA_EVENT_SWEEP_INTERVAL if you set a strict
    ARCANA_EVENT_MAX_SIZE_MB.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.4.0.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Sat, 25 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.15.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Append-only event log: every material bus action (registrations,
    sends, publishes, subscribe/unsubscribe, freezes, auth failures,
    server lifecycle) is recorded as a metadata-only event.
  * Default storage: $ARCANA_STATE_DIR/events/ (daily JSONL files,
    gzipped after 2 days, purged after 90 days).
  * New env knobs: ARCANA_EVENT_LOG_DIR, ARCANA_EVENT_COMPRESS_AGE_DAYS,
    ARCANA_EVENT_RETAIN_DAYS, ARCANA_EVENT_ARCHIVE_DIR,
    ARCANA_EVENT_MAX_SIZE_MB, ARCANA_EVENT_SWEEP_INTERVAL,
    ARCANA_EVENT_LOG_DISABLE.
  * REST: GET /events?type=...&subject=...&since=...&limit=...
  * MCP: arcana_events tool.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.3.0.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000

arcana (0.14.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: new address scheme. Agents are plain names ("alice").
    Services are "owner:capability" ("arcana:echo", "openai:chat",
    "alice:memo"). Reads possessively: left owns right.
  * Drop redundant :agent / :service suffixes from all addresses.
  * Kind is now derived from address syntax (colon = service).
  * Built-in services re-addressed: arcana:echo, arcana:markdown,
    arcana:registry, openai:chat, openai:tts, openai:embed,
    anthropic:chat, gemini:chat, runware:image.
  * Snapshot loader auto-migrates pre-0.14 addresses. Tolerance
    will be removed in 0.15.
  * Depends on arcana-core ~> 0.2.0.

 -- trans <transfire@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

